HEADWORD: Slatter
<hw>Slat"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[E.
<ets>slat</ets> to throw or dash about.]</ety> <def>To be careless,
negligent, or awkward, esp. with regard to dress and neatness; to be
wasteful.</def> <rj><au>Ray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

